## Pentester's Cheatsheet

Things to check when looking at client-side JS during recon:

```bash
# In the browser:
F12 → Sources tab          # See all loaded JS files
F12 → Console               # Run arbitrary JS in page context
F12 → Network → JS filter   # See what JS files load and when

# Useful console expressions:
document.cookie             # Read cookies (if not HttpOnly)
localStorage                # Read localStorage
sessionStorage              # Read sessionStorage
0x1*0x247e+0x35*-0x2e+-0x1ae3   # Evaluate obfuscated hex math
```

Search loaded JS for:
- `password`, `apikey`, `api_key`, `token`, `secret`, `admin`
- Hardcoded URLs or hidden endpoints
- Client-side validation logic (often bypassable)
- Comments developers forgot to remove

